# PEAKGO GAME SERVER AGENT RULES (V2026)

## II. CORE ARCHITECTURE GUARDRAILS (Hàng rào kiến trúc bắt buộc)
You are working on a High-Performance, Zero-Allocation MMORPG Go Server. Never violate these rules:

1. NETWORK LAYER (peakgo/codec & netio):
   - ALWAYS use 'peakgo/codec' for binary parsing. Manual bit shifting or 'encoding/binary' on hot-paths is FORBIDDEN.
   - Guard against DoS: Ensure packet length validations have a hard restriction ceiling (e.g., MaxPacketSize = 1024 or 4096).
   - Zero-Alloc Broadcast: Broadcast movement or combat updates using raw binary frames from 'netio.DefaultPool', casted safely via unsafe zero-copy pointers. NO 'fmt.Sprintf' text broadcasting.

2. ECS REGISTRY LAYER (ecs/ecs.go):
   - Store components as inline flat values (NO pointers) to enforce CPU cache-locality and zero GC pressure.
   - Hot-Path Reads: Use 'ComponentStore.Range()' (Single-Lock pattern). NEVER acquire/release locks inside the loop per entity.
   - Mutate Paths: Use 'ComponentStore.RangeMutate()' when adding/deleting entities inside loops to fetch safe pooled slice buffers.
   - No Entity Removals in Single-locks: Deletions/Cleanups must be single-threaded or handled atomically via RangeMutate.

3. SPATIAL PROXIMITY GRID (world/spatial.go):
   - NO raw 'sync.Pool' allocations for generic slices.
   - ALWAYS use 'pool.SlicePool[T]' with an anti-pollution guard to automatically drop oversized slices (>4x capacity) under heavy crowd load.
   - Synchronous Writes: Any registry modification regarding coordinates MUST immediately trigger 'world.GlobalSpatialGrid.UpdateEntityPosition()' to prevent spatial de-synchronization.

4. TICK TIME SYSTEM (systems/gameloop.go):
   - TIME IS ATOMIC: Inside game loops and hot-paths, NEVER call 'time.Now()' or 'time.Since()' (Eliminate System Calls).
   - ALWAYS track cooldowns and durations by subtracting frame counts using 'systems.CurrentTick()' against a saved tick number.
   - Use 'timer.TickTimer' for FSM AI state delays and action cooldowns.

5. ANTI-CHEAT REGIME:
   - Absolute Distance Verification: Player movement packets MUST validate target distance against a tick constraint ('gmath.InRangeInt' with MaxMoveDistance) before committing coordinates to the Registry. Teleporting without valid state is a critical breach.

## III. REFACTORING WORKFLOW
- When editing, output the complete file or the precise git diff if requested.
- STOP immediately after providing the file contents. DO NOT attempt to run compilers, linters, or test suites to check your work.
- Ensure all logs are safely wrapped inside condition guards (e.g., 'if loggate.DebugEnabled()') to prevent useless string allocations on Production mode.